<br>
You don't get the benefit of the &quot;You duck in to the shadows&quot; message, and I'm not clear if the &quot;Sneak&quot; message is accurate, either.  Basically, that entails targeting a less-than-indifferent mob, hitting hide until you are indifferent (showing success - the only way to know!), and then hitting sneak.  If you're REALLY lucky, you will actually stay hidden.  Otherwise, you get the &quot;You have moved and you are no longer hidden!&quot; message.<br>
<br>
I'm going to try this out with my druid tonight and see.  I'm not sure if this is at as &quot;high a level&quot; of invisibility as a rogue's sneak/hide would be, but it can't be too hard to find out.<br>
<br>
Also, for an AWESOME reference for Roguely matters, check out www.thesafehouse.org .  I basically put Rukog on hiatus for several months when I fell in love with Gawin.  Great resources there, and you'll learn everything you ever wanted to know about rogues.<br>
<br>
Happy backstabbing! <p>Rukog DethBryngr<BR>
